// Hand-maintained: NOT generated by mmtorust.
//
// Rust port of `OMCompiler/Compiler/SimCode/SerializeSparsityPattern.mo`.
// The package serializes each Jacobian's sparsity pattern and coloring to
// `<fileNamePrefix>_Jac<matrixName>.bin` next to the generated simulation
// code; the simulation runtime reads the file back when the Jacobian is
// evaluated.  Its two `external "C"` functions (`serializeJ`, `serializeC`)
// exist only as inline C snippets inside the .mo's `Include` annotation, so
// mmtorust could only emit `todo!()` for them — this module is hand-written
// and `SerializeSparsityPattern` is listed in `HANDWRITTEN_TOP_PACKAGES`
// (mmtorust/src/codegen.rs) to skip its codegen.
//
// File format (mirroring the C snippets exactly): a flat sequence of
// native-endian `unsigned int`s —
//
//   1. the leadindex: for each entry of `columnPointers` (a leading 0
//      followed by the per-column non-zero counts), the running sum so far;
//   2. the row index of every non-zero, column by column;
//   3. appended afterwards, one block per color: the column indices of that
//      color.
//
// We use `u32::to_ne_bytes` because the C version `fwrite`s raw
// `unsigned int` memory and the file is consumed by the simulation runtime
// on the same machine.  The C version throws via `throwStreamPrint` on
// open/write failures; here the writers return `Result` instead (their
// registry entries in mmtorust/src/external_c_calls.rs are `Fallible`).

